						<div class="postbody">I doubt it streams samples from CD while playing the song as the CD must be free for loading. Also I believe if you get a PSF rip you can hear the whole song which would seem to mean to me that the whole song is in memory. It may be possible that the main RAM could be used to load new samples into sound RAM when needed if more memory was needed for the song. 
<br />
<br />Alot of RPGs are similar on PS1 since it is critical to have the CD free for loading assets in battle since you have no chance of loading every single possible asset that may be used into memory.</div>

