				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">how many [PlayStation] games actually uses CDROM steaming for sound during gameplay ?</div>
<br />Zoop, Geom Cube (Blockout sequel), and Forsaken (Descent clone) use Red Book audio. Super Puzzle Fighter II Turbo (Baku Baku Animal clone) uses XA compressed audio. DDR 4th Mix and the US version (called Konamix) use VAG compressed audio.
<br />
<br />If you can hear the music in a CD player, it's a Red Book stream. If you lift the lid and the music stops or stalls, it's probably a compressed stream.</div>

