				<span class="postdetails">
					<br /><b>Joined:</b> Sun Sep 19, 2004 11:12 pm<br /><b>Posts:</b> 12424<br /><b>Location:</b> NE Indiana, USA (NTSC)
				</span>

			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The 4x DVD-ROM in the PlayStation 2 console transfers data at about 5 MB per second. A CD-quality VAG compressed audio stream like that seen in DDR series or Katamari series is 50 KB per second. So every 15 seconds or so, the drive just has to take a break from whatever level data it's streaming and go grab another 750 KB of audio from the disc.
<br />
<br />In addition to the XA music (each BGM in both arcade-accurate version and a reperformed version optimized for home TV speakers), Super Puzzle Fighter II Turbo likewise has a Red Book extra: an instrumental version of the song that plays as a reward for completing all 48 "Street Puzzle" (mission mode) levels.
<br />
<br />Any idea where I should split the discussion of optical disc technologies?</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

