					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It's the seek times that can really hit you, not the specifically linear reading rate of data.
<br />
<br /> I also read that quite a few PSP games stream ADPCM music. Whether this is stored in ram or streamed off the disc - I'm not sure. I would assume it's not ram because of the small amount, but given the battery life for constantly accessing the disc and that the PSP has a synth unit (same as the PS1 version?) - this doesn't seem likely. Maybe somebody here experienced with PSP game hacking or development can comment on this?</div>

